The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Kochi, June 6: Infosys is likely to visit colleges for fresh hiring in January next year. Most probably we will be going to campuses in January after we assess the situation. There is a slowdown now, but if the situation improves, we will be going to campuses, Infosys CEO and managing director S. Gopalakrishnan said. Infosys has been delaying campus recruitments this year.                             
	 Mumbai, June 6: The countrys forex reserves rose $1.66 billion to $262.30 billion, for the week ended May 29, compared with $260.63 billion in the previous week. Reserves had gone up $6 billion for the week ended May 22 after falling $1.73 billion in the week before. Foreign currency assets, during the week, jumped to $251.45 billion, up $1.29 billion, compared with $250.16 billion in the previous week.                            
	 Calcutta, June 6: Mukul Roy, minister of state for shipping, today met senior officials of Calcutta Port Trust and said he would look into the pending projects and issues concerning the port. This was the first meeting of the minister with us and we have updated him about the issues which the port is trying to grapple with, a top port official said.                                                                                                                           
